caption.text:
Blue
La petite mort; mortal pleasure
Brahma and Shiva in a combo
Docile with an ongoing quest of rage
Aren't you tired of the vast monotony?
Blindy honest, slaughtered the unlucky, yet provided millions
Veiled with your stunning dress, robe bleue
Flaunted the unbearable stains, cleansed the rotten spots
Ah, no wonder you are my dearest
Nereus

Left naked without the thrill,
Shaved by my own imbecility,
Barefooted while the memories bleed,
Only the chrome-hued undergarment was left; Everglow, your glare remains. 
Bitterly reminiscent, dimly sparkling, lit by the sour aftertaste.
Everlasting, timeless, undying.
